        <updateDate>2021-08-12T16:55:51Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Expanding Access to Lending Options Act </b></p> <p>This bill allows the National Credit Union Administration Board to increase the federal credit union loan maturity cap from 15 to 20 years. It also removes as a requirement for a mortgage from a credit union that a property must be a credit union member's principal residence.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
